Among Karsner's works are: 
                Debs: His Authorized Life and Letters from Woodstock Prison to Atlanta (1919); 
                Horace Traubel: His Life and Work (1919); 
                Talks with Debs in Terre Haute (and Letters from Lindlahr) (1922); 
                Sixteen Authors to One (1928); 
                Andrew Jackson: The Gentle Savage (1929);and 
                Silver Dollar: The Story of the Tabors (1932).
